      1          /**
      2           *  @file       
      3           *
      4           *  @brief      Implementation of the BackgroundThreads feature
      5           *
      6           *  @details    This module creates a pool of Background threads depending by the items present in the
      7           *              BACKGROUNDTHREADS_STACK_LIST configuration, that contain a list of stack size for each thread.
      8           *              BACKGROUNDTHREADS_MAX_STACK_SIZE macro shall be defined to be at least equal to the sum of all stacks
      9           *              listed in BACKGROUNDTHREADS_STACK_LIST.
     10           *
     11           *              Enable this module defining BACKGROUNDTHREADS_FEATURE as ENABLED in SystemConfig_prm.h
     12           *
     13           *              ** If BACKGROUNDTHREADS_MAX_STACK_SIZE cannot fit all thread stacks defined, no Background threads
     14           *              ** will be created.
     15           *
     16           *              ** Stack RAM occupation will be incremented by (number of threads + 1)*4 bytes to add
     17           *              ** stack check keywords for each thread and at the end of the entire area.
     18           *
     19           *              -  Any module can request to run a Background function using BackgroundThreads__Run(&FunctionName, minStack)
     20           *              -  Any module can also request to reserve a Thread to run a specific Background function
     21           *                 using BackgroundThreads__ReserveThread(&FunctionName, minStack) and first free thread
     22           *                 with the minimum stack size higher than the minStack value.
     23           *                 Each function can be reserved on one thread only.
     24           *              -  If a module wants to free a reserved Thread it can call BackgroundThreads__ReleaseThread(&FunctionName)
     25           *              -  BackgroundThreads__IsRunning(&FunctionName) will return if a function is running
     26           *              -  BackgroundThreads__GetElapsedTime(&FunctionName) will return time since it started, 0 otherwise
     27           *
     28           *              FunctionName shall be defined as: void FunctionName(void)
     29           *
     30           *  @copyright  Copyright 2021 Whirlpool Corporation. All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL
     31           */
